		"purpose": "Canonical reference composition for a landing page, captured 1:1 from the Figma 'Landingpage - Examples' page. Shows the vorbildliche Anordnung: hero (centered heading + Brand/Filled button group) → media-text rows (alternating) → image-teaser grid → card-teaser grid → wide highlight card → closing CTA (centered heading + Brand button). Assemble new landing pages by following this structure, drawing patterns from landingpage/block-patterns.json and atomic blocks from landingpage/blocks.json.",
		"source": "Figma file uI6oKmJ0qDhsEuE0nFah2W, node 362:1807 (Landingpage - Examples) → frame 362:3257 (Contentpage); patterns 730:21779, blocks 730:14782.",
		"conventions": "Concept Heading/Body (never raw Text). Centered contentWidth 'Medium (1024)'. Hero = centered Heading + button group (Brand primary + Filled secondary), no description. Teaser = kicker? + Heading + description + optional Tag+meta + Link. Feature/teaser grids use image-top teasers or card teasers (NOT icon+heading cards). Media-text rows alternate image side; 50-50 grid, gap xl; text column fillHeight. One wide highlight Card may sit between grids. Closing CTA = centered Heading + a single Brand Button. Zebra: canvas → surface alternation. Section title = h2; teaser/media-text headings = h3, compact card titles = h4. Header shows app name + other pages (no 'Startseite'); meta-nav + action icons off."
	},
